text: I’m reminded of a time when a buddy of mine used to play fulminator mage in a reanimator deck. He only ever used it as a stone rain, casting it and immediately Saccing it. If you’re not doing anything with the body, why not just play the actual spell. For 5 mana and all those hoops you have to jump through to make the cavalier worth it, there are so many more things you can bring doing with better effects. The reason Brainstorm is so good in 60-card formats don’t translate to 100-card Singleton. You can think they do, but they don’t. Brainstorm is also hyper efficient where the cavalier is not
